\b\i NOT IMPLEMENTED\par
\pard\b0\i0 1. On home page, type a search query in "Search" edit field in accordance with the following rules:\par
\i <keyword> \i0 includes a keyword in search results\par
\i -<keyword> \i0 excludes a keyword from search results\par
\i category:<category_name> \i0 includes a category/keyword/tag/user in search results\par
\i -category:<category_name> \i0 excludes a category/keyword/tag/user from search results\par
\i tag:<tag_value> \i0 includes a tag in search results\par
\i -tag:<tag_value> \i0 excludes a tag from search results\par
\i user:<user_name> \i0 includes a user in search results\par
\i -user:<user_name> \i0 excludes a user from search results\par
Listing a few criteria delimited by space (e.g. "\i category:nature category:art\i0 ") acts as logical AND, i.e. the resulting videos must fall both in art and nature category.\par
Listing a few criteria inside curved brackets (e.g.  "\i\{category:nature category:art\}\i0 ") acts as logical OR, i.e. search query returns all the videos in art and nature categories.\par
Example:\par
\i "villa -hotel category:tourism \{tag:Croatia tag:Dalmatia\} user:seleniumTestUser"\par
\i0 2. Click "Search" button.\par
\pard\sl240\slmult1 3. Check that all the videos on the page match the search criteria (contain the search term).\lang1049\f1\fs24\par
\pard\par
